<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <%- include('./partials/bootstrap.ejs') %>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./stylesheets/shop.css">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('./partials/header.ejs') %>
    <main>
        <div class="main1">
            <h1>Shop</h1>
            <p>Today, the fashion world has evolved, and there is no just 'for men' or 'for women.' Unisex trends are topping the
            charts, be it clothing or accessories. Men and women are both breaking the usual fashion norms and experimenting with
            all kinds of accessories. And watches are no exception. If you too want to step out of your comfort zone, you can now go
            for stylish branded watches from SUGGO</p>
        </div>
        <div class="main2">
            <div class="main2_1">
                <h3 style="display: inline;">Filter</h3>
                <a href="">clear filter</a>
                <div >
                    <h5>Categories</h5>
                    <div>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        <label for="">men</label>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        <label for="">women</label>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        <label for="">kids</label>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        <label for="">couples</label>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="products">
                <div class="sortby">
                    <select name="" id="">
                        <option value="">Popular</option>
                        <option value="">Most selled</option>
                    </select>
                    <p>Showing <% if (locals.products) { %>
                        <%= products.length  %>
                    <% } else { %>
                        0
                    <% } %> Products</p>
                </div>
                <div class="productsdisplay">
                    <% locals.products.forEach(element => { %>
                        <div class="gridborder">
                            <div >
                                <img class="shopimage" src="data:image/png;base64,<%= element.img[0].data %>" alt="<%= element.productname %>">
                            </div>
                            <a  style="text-decoration: none;color: black;display: block;font-weight: bold;" href="/shop/view/<%= element._id %>"><p class="textoverflow"><%= element.productname %></p></a>
                            <p style="color: gray;"><%= element.category %></p>
                            <p>â‚¹<%= element.price %></p>
                        </div>
                    <% }) %>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
    <%- include('./partials/footer.ejs') %>
</body>
</html>